# SecureService

SecureService is a security-oriented backend system designed as part of
my backend capability reconstruction journey toward becoming a
**Security-Focused Backend Engineer in Japan**.

This project is not a CRUD exercise, but a structural security foundation
emphasizing:

- Secure authentication architecture
- Clean layered design
- Concurrency-safe data integrity
- Unified exception boundary control
- Consistent API response protocol
- Sensitive data protection
- Verifiable security guarantees through integration testing

The goal is to gradually evolve this system into a **production-grade secure backend template**.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

## Professional Positioning

**Target Role:**
Security-Oriented Backend Engineer (Open to General Backend Roles)

This project demonstrates:

- Backend security architecture mindset
- REST semantic correctness
- JWT-based stateless authentication
- Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) foundation
- Concurrency-safe registration flow
- Structured error handling
- Secure password management (BCrypt)

